on": ["This is a skeleton file that can serve as a starting point for a Python\nconsole script. To run this script uncomment the following lines in the\n`[options.entry_points]` section in `setup.cfg`:\n\n```\nconsole_scripts =\n     fibonacci = dotenvhub.skeleton:run\n```\n\nThen run `pip install .` (or `pip install -e .` for editable mode)\nwhich will install the command `fibonacci` inside your current environment.\n\nBesides console scripts, the header (i.e. until `_logger`...) of this file can\nalso be used as template for Python modules.\n\nNote:\n\n: This file can be renamed depending on your needs or safely removed if not needed.\n\nReferences:\n: - <https://setuptools.pypa.io/en/latest/userguide/entry_point.html>\n  - <https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install>\n"], "functions": [{"name": "dotenvhub.app.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Wrapper allowing {func}`fib` to be called with string arguments in a CLI fashion\n\nInstead of returning the value from {func}`fib`, it prints the result to the\n`stdout` in a nicely formatted message.\n\nArgs:\n: args (List[str]): command line parameters as list of strings\n\n  : (for example `[\"--verbose\", \"42\"]`).\n", "---- Python API ----", "The functions defined in this section can be imported by users in their", "Python scripts/interactive interpreter, e.g. via", "`from dotenvhub.skeleton import fib`,", "when using this Python module as a library.", "---- CLI ----", "The functions defined in this section are wrappers around the main Python", "API allowing them to be called directly from the terminal as a CLI", "executable/script."]}, {"name": "dotenvhub.app.run", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Calls {func}`main` passing the CLI arguments extracted from {obj}`sys.argv`\n\nThis function can be used as entry point to create console scripts with setuptools.\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "dotenvhub.app.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dotenvhub.app.__copyright__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dotenvhub.app.__license__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "dotenvhub.cli_parser", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "dotenvhub.cli_parser.parse_args", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parse command line parameters\n\nArgs:\n: args (List[str]): command line parameters as list of strings\n\n  : (for example `[\"--help\"]`).\n\nReturns:\n\n: {obj}`argparse.Namespace`: command line parameters namespace\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}]}